{"LOY":[{"def":"A long, narrow spade for stony lands.","pos":""}],"LOYAL":[{"def":"Faithful to law; upholding the lawful authority; faithful and true to the lawful government; faithful to the prince or sovereign to whom one is subject; unswerving in allegiance.","pos":""},{"def":"True to any person or persons to whom one owes fidelity, especially as a wife to her husband, lovers to each other, and friend to friend; constant; faithful to a cause or a principle.","pos":""}],"LOYALIST":[{"def":"A person who adheres to his sovereign or to the lawful authority; especially, one who maintains his allegiance to his prince or government, and defends his cause in times of revolt or revolution.","pos":""}],"LOYALLY":[{"def":"In a loyal manner; faithfully.","pos":""}],"LOYALTY":[{"def":"The state or quality of being loyal; fidelity to a superior, or to duty, love, etc.","pos":""}]}